  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2007-12-18",
    "date": "2008-02-09T15:11:43Z",
    "text": "Performance Rights Act - Amends federal copyright law to: (1) grant performers of sound recordings equal rights to compensation from terrestrial broadcasters; (2) establish a flat annual fee in lieu of payment of royalties for individual terrestrial broadcast stations with gross revenues of less than $1.25 million and for non-commercial, public broadcast stations; (3) grant an exemption from royalty payments for broadcasts of religious services and for incidental uses of musical sound recordings; and (4) grant terrestrial broadcast stations that make limited feature uses of sound recordings a per program license option.\n\nProvides that nothing in this Act shall adversely affect the public performance rights or royalties payable to songwriters or copyright owners of musical works."
  },
